org.openimaj.image.processing.resize

Class FixedResizeProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.image.processing.resize.FixedResizeProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImageProcessor<FImage>, Processor<FImage>, SinglebandImageProcessor<Float,FImage>

    public class FixedResizeProcessor
extends Object
implements SinglebandImageProcessor<Float,FImage>
    A copy of the ResizeProcessor which speeds up the resize operation between images of a given size to another fixed size by caching the contribution calculations
    Author:
    Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • FixedResizeProcessor

        public FixedResizeProcessor(float srcX,
                            float srcY,
                            float newX,
                            float newY,
                            ResizeFilterFunction ff)
        Construct a fixed resize processor that will rescale the image to the given width and height with the given filter function. By default, this method will retain the image's aspect ratio.
        Parameters:
        srcX - The expected width of input images
        srcY - The expected with of output images
        newX - The new width of the image.
        newY - The new height of the image.
        ff - The filter function to use.

      • FixedResizeProcessor

        public FixedResizeProcessor(float srcX,
                            float srcY,
                            float newX,
                            float newY)
        Construct a fixed resize processor that will rescale the image to the given width and height with the default filter function. By default, this method will retain the image's aspect ratio which means that the resulting image may have dimensions less than those specified here.
        Parameters:
        srcX - The expected width of input images
        srcY - The expected height of input images
        newX - The new width of the image.
        newY - The new height of the image.
